1
00:00:47,516 --> 00:00:49,825
[birds twittering]

2
00:01:17,796 --> 00:01:19,627
[Father chopping wood]

3
00:01:49,596 --> 00:01:51,268
[cawing]

4
00:01:54,916 --> 00:01:57,953
Hansel. Gretel.

5
00:01:58,036 --> 00:02:00,994
Get up, you lazy bones.

6
00:02:01,396 --> 00:02:03,387
I'll not call you again.

7
00:02:11,716 --> 00:02:12,910
[moaning]

8
00:02:15,596 --> 00:02:18,269
Hansel. Hansel, wake up.

9
00:02:20,636 --> 00:02:22,354
[moaning]

10
00:02:32,596 --> 00:02:35,110
I was having
such a beautiful dream.

11
00:02:35,916 --> 00:02:37,634
What did you dream?

12
00:02:37,716 --> 00:02:41,026
We lived in
a beautiful castle,
you and I.

13
00:02:41,116 --> 00:02:44,108
And we each
had our own little pony
to ride.

14
00:02:45,396 --> 00:02:46,545
What else?

15
00:02:47,076 --> 00:02:50,307
We didn't have to do
any chores. None at all.

16
00:02:50,396 --> 00:02:52,546
We were a prince
and a princess, you see,

17
00:02:52,636 --> 00:02:54,831
and nobody could
tell us what to do.

18
00:02:54,956 --> 00:02:55,991
Nobody?

19
00:02:56,076 --> 00:02:57,555
[giggling]
Nobody.

20
00:02:58,116 --> 00:02:59,788
I like that dream.

21
00:03:00,636 --> 00:03:02,991
(Mother)
Hansel. Gretel.

22
00:03:03,876 --> 00:03:06,436
We're coming, Mother.
We're coming, Mother.

23
00:03:22,436 --> 00:03:24,392
But I'm still hungry.

24
00:03:24,476 --> 00:03:26,592
This is for your lunch.

25
00:03:26,756 --> 00:03:28,428
We don't need lunch later.

26
00:03:28,596 --> 00:03:30,234
We need breakfast now.

27
00:03:30,316 --> 00:03:32,546
Don't be so cheeky,
young lady.

28
00:03:33,196 --> 00:03:36,950
Besides, too much breakfast
is bad for the blood.

29
00:03:41,956 --> 00:03:43,912
That was just fine, Maria.

30
00:03:45,516 --> 00:03:46,790
Wasn't it, children?

31
00:03:47,396 --> 00:03:48,875
Yes.
Yes.

32
00:03:49,356 --> 00:03:51,108
It was fine
for a single mouse.

33
00:03:51,276 --> 00:03:53,073
Not for a man and his family.

34
00:03:55,516 --> 00:03:57,711
Go ready the cart
for our journey today.

35
00:03:59,036 --> 00:04:00,754
Yes, Father.
Yes, Father.

36
00:04:03,996 --> 00:04:06,954
Stephan, they haven't
finished the chores
I gave them.

37
00:04:07,676 --> 00:04:09,189
They can do the chores
tomorrow.

38
00:04:09,276 --> 00:04:10,834
I promised
to take them with me.

39
00:04:10,916 --> 00:04:14,113
Tomorrow, tomorrow.
Everything is always put off.

40
00:04:14,476 --> 00:04:16,706
Will we have enough to eat
on our table tomorrow?

41
00:04:16,796 --> 00:04:19,629
Oh, Stephan,
what's going to become of us?

42
00:04:19,956 --> 00:04:21,992
The four of us
are going to starve.

43
00:04:23,796 --> 00:04:27,425
You might as well
start planing the boards
for our coffins.

44
00:04:29,876 --> 00:04:31,389
Don't worry.

45
00:04:31,716 --> 00:04:34,913
I'm sure that I can
sell all the wood
that we can carry.

46
00:04:35,036 --> 00:04:38,392
Have faith.
God will not forsake us.

47
00:04:43,676 --> 00:04:44,904
[birds chirping]

48
00:04:46,716 --> 00:04:48,946
Now, be a good girl.

49
00:04:49,516 --> 00:04:51,666
Hansel, don't lose your hat.

50
00:04:52,436 --> 00:04:55,951
Stephan, don't let the baker
cheat you.

51
00:04:56,116 --> 00:04:58,994
Impossible. Duncan, come on.

52
00:04:59,076 --> 00:05:00,304
[braying]

53
00:05:03,476 --> 00:05:05,114
Bye-bye, Mother.
Bye-bye.

54
00:05:05,196 --> 00:05:06,914
Bye-bye.
Bye-bye.

55
00:05:11,396 --> 00:05:13,273
(Gretel)
Oh, ask us another one,
Father.

56
00:05:13,516 --> 00:05:15,074
(Hansel)
Yes, another riddle.

57
00:05:15,636 --> 00:05:19,629
(Father)
All right, uh, let me see.
Yes, I've got one.

58
00:05:20,196 --> 00:05:23,791
What has arms and legs
but hasn't got a head?

59
00:05:25,196 --> 00:05:26,424
Is it a fly?

60
00:05:26,516 --> 00:05:27,585
No.

61
00:05:28,076 --> 00:05:30,431
I know, I know.
It's a turtle.

62
00:05:30,836 --> 00:05:32,588
Silly, a turtle has a head.

63
00:05:32,676 --> 00:05:34,394
So does a fly, Hansel.

64
00:05:37,636 --> 00:05:39,388
(Gretel)
Oh, tell us, Father.

65
00:05:39,476 --> 00:05:42,149
What has arms, legs,
but hasn't got a head?

66
00:05:42,436 --> 00:05:43,915
(Father)
A chair.

67
00:05:43,996 --> 00:05:45,634
[Hansel and Gretel giggling]

68
00:05:45,836 --> 00:05:47,633
(Hansel)
You think that was
a hard one, Father?

69
00:05:47,796 --> 00:05:49,593
I'll stump you
with a riddle.

70
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:52,430
What two things
can you never
have for breakfast?

71
00:05:52,516 --> 00:05:54,268
Lunch and dinner.
(Gretel)
Lunch and dinner.

72
00:05:55,156 --> 00:05:56,874
[Gretel giggling]

73
00:05:59,116 --> 00:06:01,425
Come on, ducks.
Out of the way.

74
00:06:01,516 --> 00:06:03,427
[quacking]

75
00:06:03,596 --> 00:06:05,905
[ducks quacking]

76
00:06:07,116 --> 00:06:08,868
[people chattering]

77
00:06:09,796 --> 00:06:11,673
There you are.
Thank you.

78
00:06:16,036 --> 00:06:19,187
(woman)
Pure mackerel.
Pure mackerel!

79
00:06:19,276 --> 00:06:20,709
That'll do.

80
00:06:21,636 --> 00:06:22,785
Thanks.

81
00:06:24,756 --> 00:06:26,348
Hmm. Mmm?

82
00:06:30,476 --> 00:06:32,387
[vendors calling]

83
00:06:34,236 --> 00:06:35,874
[bell ringing]

84
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:44,954
[clanging]

85
00:06:50,116 --> 00:06:51,754
(woman)
Pure mackerel.

86
00:06:52,556 --> 00:06:54,274
Pure mackerel.

87
00:06:58,956 --> 00:07:00,787
Hey, woodcutter.

88
00:07:05,196 --> 00:07:06,754
[coins clinking]

89
00:07:07,236 --> 00:07:09,272
[chuckling]
Thank you, blacksmith.

90
00:07:13,676 --> 00:07:14,665
Hey.

91
00:07:24,356 --> 00:07:25,709
Thank you.

92
00:07:27,796 --> 00:07:31,789
Father, look.
The blacksmith gave me
these strange stones.

93
00:07:31,876 --> 00:07:33,275
What are they?

94
00:07:33,836 --> 00:07:35,474
These are flints.

95
00:07:35,596 --> 00:07:38,827
If you strike them together,
they make sparks
to start a fire.

96
00:07:38,956 --> 00:07:40,514
They're a good gift.

97
00:07:41,956 --> 00:07:44,595
Keep them with you always,
and you'll never be cold.

98
00:07:45,476 --> 00:07:47,194
(woman)
Pure mackerel.

99
00:07:48,156 --> 00:07:49,635
Pure mackerel.

100
00:07:59,516 --> 00:08:01,472
Children,
I told you to sit quietly

101
00:08:01,556 --> 00:08:03,433
while I finish
my business here.

102
00:08:08,436 --> 00:08:10,631
This is the last bundle, sir.

103
00:08:15,596 --> 00:08:20,067
Taste and touch nothing
or your father will
pay for your curiosity.

104
00:08:22,116 --> 00:08:24,152
And the same goes for you.

105
00:08:26,396 --> 00:08:29,672
(Father)
Sir, the wood basket's full.
I'm putting these by the oven.

106
00:08:39,076 --> 00:08:40,429
[sniffing]

107
00:09:15,396 --> 00:09:16,795
[door opening]

108
00:09:21,316 --> 00:09:22,305
[gulping]

109
00:09:26,436 --> 00:09:27,789
[drawer opening]

110
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,993
Here's your money,
woodcutter.

111
00:09:34,716 --> 00:09:36,593
Sir, this is not
what we agreed upon.

112
00:09:36,716 --> 00:09:38,308
I don't have to
deal with you at all.

113
00:09:38,396 --> 00:09:40,546
I could easily cut my own wood
for my oven.

114
00:09:41,076 --> 00:09:43,988
But I haven't the time,
so you reap the benefits.

115
00:09:44,076 --> 00:09:45,748
Sir, the last time
I brought you wood,

116
00:09:45,836 --> 00:09:48,714
you paid me too little,
and you promised
to pay me fairly this time.

117
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:50,707
I think you're mistaken,
woodcutter.

118
00:09:50,876 --> 00:09:52,832
I don't remember
any such thing.

119
00:09:54,276 --> 00:09:55,595
Little girl.

120
00:10:00,316 --> 00:10:01,874
And for you,

121
00:10:01,956 --> 00:10:05,346
some delicious cookie crumbs.

122
00:10:13,636 --> 00:10:15,069
What do you say, Gretel?

123
00:10:16,236 --> 00:10:18,352
Thank you, Master baker, sir.

124
00:10:22,836 --> 00:10:25,873
You're very welcome, child.

125
00:10:26,316 --> 00:10:28,147
Come along, children.

126
00:10:34,916 --> 00:10:36,713
Red and yellow ribbons.

127
00:10:36,796 --> 00:10:38,548
Come see and come buy.

128
00:10:39,516 --> 00:10:42,076
A ribbon in the hair
always lights up the eye.

129
00:10:42,156 --> 00:10:44,795
[people chattering]
My, what beautiful hair
this child has.

130
00:10:44,876 --> 00:10:47,470
How pretty her hair would look
with a ribbon or two in it.

131
00:10:47,556 --> 00:10:49,194
This one's nice,

132
00:10:49,276 --> 00:10:52,552
but perhaps
a blue satin ribbon
to tie up her hair?

133
00:10:54,516 --> 00:10:56,029
No, thank you.

134
00:10:57,956 --> 00:10:59,594
Children,
why don't you go along

135
00:10:59,676 --> 00:11:01,348
and watch
the Punch and Judy show?

136
00:11:13,996 --> 00:11:16,590
(man)
Fish. Fresh fish.

137
00:11:17,156 --> 00:11:18,874
Get your fish here.

138
00:11:20,396 --> 00:11:22,114
Come on. Fish here.

139
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:26,749
Hello, children,
wouldn't you like
some fresh mackerel?

140
00:11:26,836 --> 00:11:28,110
No, thank you.
Fresh from the sea.

141
00:11:28,196 --> 00:11:31,188
(man #2)
Boysenberry honey.
The fruit of the bee.

142
00:11:31,876 --> 00:11:33,946
Ah, children, golden honey.

143
00:11:34,036 --> 00:11:35,435
The sweet fruit of the bee.

144
00:11:35,516 --> 00:11:38,235
Mmm-hmm.
Delicious. Go on, try it.
Sorry. No, thank you.

145
00:11:38,316 --> 00:11:40,625
...very special,
that's right.
Nice.

146
00:11:40,716 --> 00:11:41,785
They look lovely.

147
00:11:41,876 --> 00:11:43,992
And another bunch of red roses
for your wife?

148
00:11:44,076 --> 00:11:45,748
(man #3)
No, my dear.
Thanks anyway.

149
00:11:45,956 --> 00:11:48,186
(woman)
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪

150
00:11:48,276 --> 00:11:50,585
(Punch)
♪ Turn you head and slap,
slap, slap ♪

151
00:11:50,676 --> 00:11:52,712
♪ Left and right,
left and then ♪

152
00:11:52,796 --> 00:11:55,435
♪ 'Round about
and back again ♪

153
00:11:55,516 --> 00:11:59,475
♪♪[accordion playing]

154
00:11:59,636 --> 00:12:01,911
♪ I would like to
dance with him ♪

155
00:12:01,996 --> 00:12:04,191
♪ He is nice and tall
and slim ♪

156
00:12:04,276 --> 00:12:05,994
What's your name, little boy?

157
00:12:06,156 --> 00:12:07,475
Hansel.

158
00:12:07,556 --> 00:12:09,786
(Judy)
♪ Hansel, dear,
would you agree? ♪

159
00:12:09,876 --> 00:12:12,231
♪ Would you dance
a dance with me? ♪

160
00:12:14,476 --> 00:12:16,706
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪

161
00:12:16,796 --> 00:12:18,548
♪ Point your toe
and tap, tap, tap ♪

162
00:12:19,476 --> 00:12:20,670
(Judy)
Naughty boy.

163
00:12:21,236 --> 00:12:25,991
♪ Left and right,
left and then
'Round about and back again ♪

164
00:12:27,636 --> 00:12:30,025
(Punch)
Listen to my poem, everybody.

165
00:12:30,276 --> 00:12:34,554
♪ ''A fool who's never
changed his mind and who can
think it strange? ♪

166
00:12:34,676 --> 00:12:38,954
♪ The reason's clear,
for fools, my friends,
have not a mind to change'' ♪

167
00:12:39,036 --> 00:12:41,550
[kids laughing]
Ouch.

168
00:12:41,636 --> 00:12:43,991
Come on, Punch, dear.
Let's sing our song.

169
00:12:44,076 --> 00:12:46,306
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪

170
00:12:46,396 --> 00:12:48,512
♪ Point your toe
and tap, tap, tap ♪

171
00:12:48,596 --> 00:12:50,746
♪ Left and right,
left and then ♪

172
00:12:50,836 --> 00:12:53,225
♪ 'Round about
and back again ♪

173
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:55,824
Come on, everybody,
let's all sing.

174
00:12:56,356 --> 00:12:58,950
[kids cheering]

175
00:13:01,196 --> 00:13:03,551
(all)
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪

176
00:13:03,636 --> 00:13:05,831
♪ Point your toe
and tap, tap, tap ♪

177
00:13:05,916 --> 00:13:07,668
♪ Left and right,
left and then ♪

178
00:13:07,756 --> 00:13:10,509
♪ 'Round about
and back again ♪

179
00:13:10,596 --> 00:13:12,826
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪

180
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:15,032
♪ Point your toe
and tap, tap, tap ♪

181
00:13:15,116 --> 00:13:19,632
♪ Left and right,
left and then
turn about up in the air ♪♪

182
00:13:19,716 --> 00:13:22,992
♪♪[all continue singing]

183
00:14:14,716 --> 00:14:16,468
[birds twittering]

184
00:14:25,516 --> 00:14:27,393
[sobbing]

185
00:14:29,036 --> 00:14:30,549
[bell ringing]

186
00:15:09,196 --> 00:15:11,152
(Gretel)
Mama. Oh, Mama.

187
00:15:11,556 --> 00:15:14,070
We sang with Punch and Judy.
Really.

188
00:15:14,356 --> 00:15:16,392
(Hansel)
Yes, we learned to dance
from the puppets.

189
00:15:16,716 --> 00:15:18,547
Punch and Judy were so funny.

190
00:15:18,636 --> 00:15:22,106
All they did was fight
and hit each other
with a rolling pin.

191
00:15:23,396 --> 00:15:26,149
The blacksmith gave me
two stones that make fire.

192
00:15:26,236 --> 00:15:29,148
Do you want to hear me sing
the song I learned, Mama?

193
00:15:29,236 --> 00:15:31,033
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪♪

194
00:15:31,116 --> 00:15:32,390
No, not now, Gretel.

195
00:15:32,516 --> 00:15:34,347
Look at the beautiful stones.

196
00:15:34,516 --> 00:15:36,393
Father told me
how to use them.

197
00:15:36,476 --> 00:15:40,151
Take your sister inside.
Go on. Go on.

198
00:15:56,356 --> 00:15:58,551
This doesn't taste
like the soup,

199
00:15:58,716 --> 00:16:00,832
it tastes like
the wash water.

200
00:16:00,916 --> 00:16:02,395
[laughing]

201
00:16:03,556 --> 00:16:06,946
I don't think you know
what the wash water
tastes like.

202
00:16:07,036 --> 00:16:10,267
I tried it once.
I really did.

203
00:16:12,036 --> 00:16:13,867
Stop it. Stop it.

204
00:16:14,676 --> 00:16:16,826
How dare you
laugh at this meal.

205
00:16:17,916 --> 00:16:20,146
Next time, I'll eat
the last potato myself.

206
00:16:21,876 --> 00:16:23,594
Children, go to bed.

207
00:16:24,796 --> 00:16:26,673
Yes, go to bed, children.

208
00:16:26,836 --> 00:16:29,031
And if you're lucky,
you'll never wake up.

209
00:16:43,996 --> 00:16:46,635
Maria, how could
you say such a thing?

210
00:16:46,716 --> 00:16:50,231
How could
you let that fat baker
cheat you again?

211
00:16:51,276 --> 00:16:53,710
Are you
a stupid simpleton?

212
00:16:54,356 --> 00:16:56,312
I'm a simple woodcutter.

213
00:16:56,396 --> 00:16:58,034
You're a father.

214
00:16:59,476 --> 00:17:01,785
Haven't you the courage
to stand up to someone

215
00:17:01,876 --> 00:17:04,868
who's taking the food
from your wife and babies

216
00:17:04,956 --> 00:17:07,948
by not paying you
what is rightfully
owed to you?

217
00:17:09,636 --> 00:17:11,467
He's an important man
in town.

218
00:17:11,556 --> 00:17:13,865
I don't care
if he's the King.

219
00:17:16,076 --> 00:17:19,705
I'll go to the town myself
and speak to the baker.

220
00:17:21,356 --> 00:17:23,586
All right, I've heard enough.

221
00:17:25,636 --> 00:17:27,467
I'll go in tomorrow

222
00:17:27,916 --> 00:17:31,147
and I will collect the rest
of what is owed to me.

223
00:17:37,076 --> 00:17:38,589
[birds chirping]

224
00:17:38,676 --> 00:17:39,950
[horse neighing]

225
00:17:43,636 --> 00:17:44,785
Mama.

226
00:17:46,036 --> 00:17:47,151
Mama?

227
00:17:57,316 --> 00:17:59,034
Good morning, missus.

228
00:17:59,196 --> 00:18:00,868
Good morning to you,
neighbour.

229
00:18:00,956 --> 00:18:03,186
I've brought
some things for you.

230
00:18:05,756 --> 00:18:08,145
Our cows has been
producing more milk

231
00:18:08,236 --> 00:18:10,545
than we can drink
or make cheese with.

232
00:18:11,116 --> 00:18:12,754
I've brought you
some eggs, too.

233
00:18:12,876 --> 00:18:14,548
l--I have no money
for this, neighbour.

234
00:18:14,636 --> 00:18:15,864
Oh, no need.

235
00:18:15,956 --> 00:18:19,187
Your good husband
has done me favours
many a time.

236
00:18:19,276 --> 00:18:23,554
Why, just last winter,
when I was sick
and couldn't get out of bed,

237
00:18:24,356 --> 00:18:27,905
he brought
firewood to my family
to keep my home warm.

238
00:18:28,596 --> 00:18:31,235
He's a good neighbour
and a good man.

239
00:18:31,316 --> 00:18:33,910
Yes, my husband
cares for everyone.

240
00:18:33,996 --> 00:18:36,385
But this is very kind
of you and your family.

241
00:18:36,476 --> 00:18:38,706
This is heavy. I'll carry it.

242
00:18:38,796 --> 00:18:40,070
Thank you.

243
00:18:45,676 --> 00:18:49,749
You know, yesterday,
when I was delivering
milk to the miller,

244
00:18:50,036 --> 00:18:53,108
he told me that another child
has disappeared

245
00:18:53,196 --> 00:18:55,426
into that cursed North Woods.

246
00:18:57,196 --> 00:18:59,630
They looked hard all day
for that little boy.

247
00:19:00,476 --> 00:19:02,114
Found nothing.

248
00:19:02,876 --> 00:19:04,514
That's terrible.

249
00:19:05,036 --> 00:19:07,470
lf you ask me, my thought is

250
00:19:07,676 --> 00:19:10,713
no one will ever see
that child again, missus.

251
00:19:11,876 --> 00:19:15,425
Look, children.
Fresh milk and some eggs.

252
00:19:17,556 --> 00:19:19,990
Thank you.
Say thank you, children.

253
00:19:20,116 --> 00:19:21,435
Thank you.
Thank you.

254
00:19:21,516 --> 00:19:22,790
Good day.

255
00:19:34,476 --> 00:19:37,115
Mmm, this cream is delicious.

256
00:19:40,116 --> 00:19:41,595
Mmm.

257
00:19:45,956 --> 00:19:48,424
I'm going to make us
some custard.

258
00:19:49,196 --> 00:19:50,675
I can't wait.

259
00:20:25,116 --> 00:20:27,072
[exclaiming]

260
00:20:28,116 --> 00:20:29,344
Mmm.

261
00:20:30,156 --> 00:20:33,034
This custard would be perfect
with some berries.

262
00:20:33,116 --> 00:20:36,392
I'm going to find some
if I have to search
the forest high and low.

263
00:20:36,476 --> 00:20:38,228
And we're going to have
a real celebration

264
00:20:38,316 --> 00:20:39,829
when your father
gets home tonight.

265
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:41,634
Oh, I'm so happy.

266
00:20:43,196 --> 00:20:47,075
Now, Gretel, while I'm gone,
you do your darning.

267
00:20:47,156 --> 00:20:48,145
Yes, Mama.

268
00:20:48,236 --> 00:20:51,273
And Hansel,
make sure that weave
is good and tight

269
00:20:51,356 --> 00:20:52,709
or else the broom won't last.

270
00:20:52,796 --> 00:20:54,354
And Hansel,
please do not forget

271
00:20:54,436 --> 00:20:55,949
to give some
water to the donkey.

272
00:20:56,036 --> 00:20:57,185
I won't forget.

273
00:21:05,356 --> 00:21:07,392
[birds twittering]

274
00:21:23,276 --> 00:21:25,267
[bell ringing]

275
00:21:33,076 --> 00:21:34,794
♪♪[Hansel whistling]

276
00:21:48,876 --> 00:21:51,071
♪♪[Gretel humming]

277
00:21:51,156 --> 00:21:52,828
May I have this dance, miss?

278
00:21:52,916 --> 00:21:54,429
Yes, kind sir.

279
00:21:55,916 --> 00:21:58,146
♪ Gretel, dear,
I don't know how ♪

280
00:21:58,236 --> 00:22:00,511
♪ When to turn
and how to bow ♪

281
00:22:00,596 --> 00:22:02,905
♪ Show me what I ought to do ♪

282
00:22:02,996 --> 00:22:05,226
♪ So that I may
dance with you ♪

283
00:22:07,636 --> 00:22:10,025
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪

284
00:22:10,116 --> 00:22:12,471
♪ Point your toe
and tap, tap, tap ♪

285
00:22:12,556 --> 00:22:14,865
♪ Left and right,
left and then ♪

286
00:22:14,956 --> 00:22:17,151
♪ 'Round about
and back again ♪

287
00:22:17,236 --> 00:22:19,591
(both)
♪ Raise your hands
and clap, clap, clap ♪

288
00:22:19,676 --> 00:22:21,871
♪ Point your toe
and tap, tap, tap ♪

289
00:22:21,956 --> 00:22:24,265
♪ Left and right,
left and then ♪

290
00:22:24,356 --> 00:22:26,551
♪ 'Round about
and back again ♪♪

291
00:22:26,636 --> 00:22:29,673
♪♪[continue singing]

292
00:22:59,036 --> 00:23:01,152
[birds chirping]

293
00:23:12,436 --> 00:23:14,552
♪♪[singing]

294
00:23:31,116 --> 00:23:32,708
[clattering]

295
00:23:35,876 --> 00:23:37,104
Oh, no!

296
00:23:38,916 --> 00:23:40,554
This is terrible!

297
00:23:41,596 --> 00:23:43,473
Hansel,
what are we going to do?

298
00:23:43,636 --> 00:23:45,513
All the milk is spilt.

299
00:23:45,916 --> 00:23:48,384
I must have left
the barn door open.

300
00:23:53,796 --> 00:23:55,354
What are we going
to tell Mother?

301
00:23:55,996 --> 00:23:57,224
I don't know.

302
00:23:57,316 --> 00:23:58,635
Look, get it cleared up.

303
00:23:58,716 --> 00:24:00,195
I'm getting him out of here.

304
00:24:02,596 --> 00:24:05,064
Please, Duncan, move.
Come on.

305
00:24:08,676 --> 00:24:10,109
Duncan, please.

306
00:24:11,596 --> 00:24:13,029
[birds chirping]

307
00:24:19,756 --> 00:24:21,314
(Mother)
Hansel, Gretel.

308
00:24:22,716 --> 00:24:24,195
What are you doing?

309
00:24:24,756 --> 00:24:26,712
What's the donkey
doing in the house?

310
00:24:26,796 --> 00:24:27,785
[brays]

311
00:24:35,756 --> 00:24:37,269
Where's my custard?

312
00:24:38,476 --> 00:24:39,909
[sobbing]

313
00:24:41,036 --> 00:24:43,072
We didn't see him coming in.

314
00:24:43,516 --> 00:24:48,112
You let that stupid animal
eat my custard
and drink all our milk?

315
00:24:49,196 --> 00:24:51,756
Hansel,
get that beast out of here.

316
00:24:51,836 --> 00:24:53,189
Now. Do you hear?

317
00:24:53,276 --> 00:24:56,666
Take the donkey to the barn,
you foolish boy.

318
00:24:59,036 --> 00:25:00,628
Come on, Duncan.

319
00:25:01,076 --> 00:25:02,748
[braying]

320
00:25:03,836 --> 00:25:04,985
Move, Duncan.

321
00:25:06,076 --> 00:25:08,590
I'll take the donkey myself.

322
00:25:10,076 --> 00:25:11,714
You're such
a worthless idiot.

323
00:25:11,796 --> 00:25:13,752
Come on. Out.
I've had enough.

324
00:25:13,836 --> 00:25:15,713
Just get out of my kitchen.

325
00:25:15,796 --> 00:25:18,947
Get out of here. Out!

326
00:25:19,916 --> 00:25:21,793
[braying]
Out.

327
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:28,269
You stupid, stupid children.

328
00:25:28,476 --> 00:25:30,910
I'll never forgive you,
never.

329
00:25:30,996 --> 00:25:33,749
We're sorry. We really are.

330
00:25:34,556 --> 00:25:36,467
Find some berries
for our dinner tonight.

331
00:25:36,556 --> 00:25:38,911
Enough for all of us,
or don't come back.

332
00:25:39,436 --> 00:25:41,666
Now get out of my sight.

333
00:25:43,156 --> 00:25:44,509
Get out of here.

334
00:25:44,596 --> 00:25:47,235
And don't even think
of coming back empty-handed

335
00:25:47,316 --> 00:25:48,385
or I'll--

336
00:25:48,556 --> 00:25:49,671
I'll--
Mama?

337
00:25:50,356 --> 00:25:53,666
Go away. Leave me alone.

338
00:26:18,236 --> 00:26:19,715
[birds cawing]

339
00:26:30,356 --> 00:26:32,711
Come on.
Let's go over there,
where we always go.

340
00:26:33,796 --> 00:26:36,026
There aren't any berries
left in those woods.

341
00:26:36,116 --> 00:26:37,788
We've picked them all.

342
00:26:37,876 --> 00:26:39,673
No one ever goes here.

343
00:26:39,756 --> 00:26:42,316
But Papa said not to
come in these woods.

344
00:26:42,396 --> 00:26:45,832
There's no path to follow.
We could get lost.

345
00:26:46,076 --> 00:26:49,307
Have you still got
those cookie crumbs
the baker gave you?

346
00:26:49,996 --> 00:26:52,669
Yes, but they're stale.

347
00:26:55,236 --> 00:26:58,194
Good. Just enough.

348
00:26:59,636 --> 00:27:03,754
We'll leave a trail of crumbs
so that we can find
our way back home.

349
00:27:03,956 --> 00:27:05,753
And we won't get lost.

350
00:27:06,196 --> 00:27:07,834
But Papa said--

351
00:27:07,916 --> 00:27:09,827
Come on. Don't be a baby.

352
00:27:30,196 --> 00:27:32,994
[cawing]

353
00:28:12,076 --> 00:28:13,065
[cawing]

354
00:29:07,636 --> 00:29:09,672
Look at all these berries.

355
00:29:11,076 --> 00:29:13,715
They're so big and ripe.

356
00:29:14,236 --> 00:29:15,635
Mmm, sweet, too.

357
00:29:22,556 --> 00:29:24,467
Mother's going to be pleased.

358
00:30:00,316 --> 00:30:05,185
♪ A fairy plays her harp
in the wood all day ♪

359
00:30:05,756 --> 00:30:08,316
♪ She wears a velvet mantle ♪

360
00:30:08,396 --> 00:30:11,149
♪ of rose and grey ♪

361
00:30:11,876 --> 00:30:14,595
♪ Where can this
good fairy be? ♪

362
00:30:14,676 --> 00:30:18,066
♪ Playing pretty songs
for me ♪

363
00:30:18,156 --> 00:30:23,025
♪ Maybe she lives
underneath an apple tree ♪

364
00:30:28,956 --> 00:30:31,265
♪ Her hair is black as night ♪

365
00:30:31,356 --> 00:30:34,154
♪ and her cheeks are red ♪

366
00:30:34,716 --> 00:30:37,230
♪ She wears a cap of silver ♪

367
00:30:37,316 --> 00:30:39,671
♪ upon her head ♪

368
00:30:40,516 --> 00:30:43,110
♪ Where can this
good fairy be? ♪

369
00:30:43,196 --> 00:30:45,949
♪ Waiting in the woods
for me ♪

370
00:30:46,076 --> 00:30:50,991
♪ Maybe she lives
underneath a chocolate tree ♪

371
00:30:52,476 --> 00:30:54,273
There's no such thing
as a chocolate tree.

372
00:30:54,356 --> 00:30:56,108
Yes, there is.

373
00:31:16,596 --> 00:31:19,110
♪ She dances in a circle ♪

374
00:31:19,196 --> 00:31:21,585
♪ of warm sunlight ♪

375
00:31:22,316 --> 00:31:24,546
♪ Her feet are very swift ♪

376
00:31:24,636 --> 00:31:27,548
♪ and her eyes are bright ♪

377
00:31:28,076 --> 00:31:30,829
♪ Where can this
sweet fairy be? ♪

378
00:31:30,916 --> 00:31:33,874
♪ Dancing in the sun for me ♪

379
00:31:33,956 --> 00:31:38,825
♪ Maybe she lives
underneath a chestnut tree ♪

380
00:31:39,916 --> 00:31:42,589
♪ Maybe she lives underneath ♪

381
00:31:42,676 --> 00:31:47,625
♪ a chestnut tree ♪♪

382
00:31:50,956 --> 00:31:52,594
Mother can't be
cross with us,

383
00:31:52,676 --> 00:31:54,507
with all the berries
we've picked.

384
00:31:54,876 --> 00:31:57,470
I've never made one
so lovely before.

385
00:31:58,236 --> 00:32:01,546
Well, Princess,
shall we return
to our castle?

386
00:32:02,556 --> 00:32:05,275
All we have to do
is follow our royal trail.

387
00:32:05,516 --> 00:32:07,632
Our royal trail
of cookie crumbs.

388
00:32:07,716 --> 00:32:08,910
[Gretel giggling]

389
00:32:12,076 --> 00:32:13,748
(Hansel)
Here's our trail.

390
00:32:15,916 --> 00:32:17,235
Here's another one.

391
00:32:17,316 --> 00:32:18,431
(Gretel)
There's one.

392
00:32:21,396 --> 00:32:22,545
(Hansel)
Look, some more.

393
00:32:23,956 --> 00:32:25,708
There's another one.

394
00:32:27,316 --> 00:32:28,954
And another one.

395
00:32:31,836 --> 00:32:33,747
[crows cawing]

396
00:32:54,236 --> 00:32:55,908
Where's our trail?

397
00:33:07,596 --> 00:33:08,949
It's gone.

398
00:33:12,916 --> 00:33:14,668
I think we're lost.

399
00:33:15,156 --> 00:33:16,714
Don't say that.

400
00:33:16,796 --> 00:33:19,515
We'll find our way back.
I know we will.

401
00:33:21,996 --> 00:33:23,190
Come on.

402
00:33:35,036 --> 00:33:37,311
♪ Oh, what a day,
Oh, what a day ♪

403
00:33:37,396 --> 00:33:39,546
♪ Oh, what a happy man am I ♪

404
00:33:39,636 --> 00:33:41,945
♪ Oh, what a bird,
Oh, what a breeze ♪

405
00:33:42,036 --> 00:33:44,311
♪ Oh, what a joy
to see the sky ♪

406
00:33:46,556 --> 00:33:48,831
♪ How did I know
how to be strong? ♪

407
00:33:48,916 --> 00:33:51,111
♪ Where did I find
the voice to say? ♪

408
00:33:51,196 --> 00:33:55,986
♪ No, not enough!
No, not at all!
No, not again! No, not today ♪

409
00:33:58,156 --> 00:34:02,752
♪ This is how it should be,
This is how it is ♪

410
00:34:02,836 --> 00:34:07,466
♪ A man gets what he wants
if he takes what is his ♪

411
00:34:07,556 --> 00:34:12,027
♪ Oh, what a man,
Oh, what a man,
Oh, what a noble man am I ♪

412
00:34:12,116 --> 00:34:14,425
♪ Oh, what a tree,
Oh, what a leaf ♪

413
00:34:14,516 --> 00:34:17,394
♪ Oh, what a fence,
What a cottage,
What a flower ♪

414
00:34:17,476 --> 00:34:18,829
♪ What a life ♪♪

415
00:34:18,916 --> 00:34:19,905
[gate closing]

416
00:34:37,556 --> 00:34:39,592
Maria, wake up.

417
00:34:40,276 --> 00:34:42,312
This is no time
to take a nap.

418
00:34:43,196 --> 00:34:45,710
Your husband's home
from his long trek to town.

419
00:34:45,796 --> 00:34:47,752
Would you like to see
what I bought?

420
00:34:48,796 --> 00:34:50,673
Aren't you glad
to welcome me home?

421
00:34:50,756 --> 00:34:53,554
Welcome you home to what?

422
00:34:53,796 --> 00:34:55,593
Nothing but troubles.

423
00:34:55,836 --> 00:34:59,749
I have to keep the house,
feed the children.

424
00:34:59,916 --> 00:35:01,872
On what? Nothing.

425
00:35:01,956 --> 00:35:05,585
Well, then let us see
what we have to eat today.

426
00:35:05,676 --> 00:35:07,871
Oh, Stephan, I'm in no mood
for your jokes.

427
00:35:07,956 --> 00:35:09,867
I'm weary of living.

428
00:35:10,516 --> 00:35:14,031
The cupboard is barren.
We have nothing.

429
00:35:14,116 --> 00:35:17,745
Would a large jar of honey
make you less
weary of living?

430
00:35:21,356 --> 00:35:24,871
Or wouldn't some flour
fill up our cupboard nicely?

431
00:35:25,996 --> 00:35:29,466
How about some butter?

432
00:35:30,796 --> 00:35:32,024
Butter?

433
00:35:34,276 --> 00:35:36,949
Well,
where did this come from?

434
00:35:37,036 --> 00:35:38,708
I demanded my money
from the baker

435
00:35:38,796 --> 00:35:42,425
and he gave us every
last penny he owes us.

436
00:35:42,876 --> 00:35:45,390
Oh, Stephan!

437
00:35:48,756 --> 00:35:50,314
He's a hard man.

438
00:35:50,476 --> 00:35:52,034
Did he give you any trouble?

439
00:35:52,116 --> 00:35:54,266
Mmm, yes, well,
he put up a bit of a fuss,

440
00:35:54,356 --> 00:35:56,551
but this time I didn't
let him off the hook

441
00:35:56,636 --> 00:35:58,592
until I had
everything that I came for.

442
00:35:58,676 --> 00:35:59,870
[exclaiming]

443
00:36:06,236 --> 00:36:07,271
Tea.

444
00:36:09,036 --> 00:36:10,515
Sausage.

445
00:36:11,116 --> 00:36:12,105
Mmm.

446
00:36:16,596 --> 00:36:18,348
[laughing]

447
00:36:18,796 --> 00:36:19,911
Ham.

448
00:36:21,716 --> 00:36:24,310
This must have
cost a fortune.

449
00:36:24,836 --> 00:36:26,349
Where are the children?

450
00:36:26,636 --> 00:36:28,592
Oh, those little scallywags.

451
00:36:28,676 --> 00:36:30,234
Do you know what they did?

452
00:36:30,516 --> 00:36:32,507
I left them alone,
and while I was gone,

453
00:36:32,596 --> 00:36:34,791
they let the donkey
into the house.

454
00:36:35,516 --> 00:36:38,667
He ate
an entire pan of custard
that I had made.

455
00:36:38,756 --> 00:36:40,075
And broke
a pitcher of milk

456
00:36:40,156 --> 00:36:42,465
that our neighbour
had given us
this very morning.

457
00:36:44,036 --> 00:36:47,187
When I found them playing
with the donkey in the house,

458
00:36:47,276 --> 00:36:50,951
I was so angry with them,
I sent them out
to pick berries.

459
00:36:51,076 --> 00:36:53,544
There aren't many berries
left on the bushes
by the cottage.

460
00:36:53,636 --> 00:36:54,751
We've eaten them all.

461
00:36:54,836 --> 00:36:57,191
Yes, I know.
I couldn't find any myself.

462
00:36:57,276 --> 00:36:59,346
But I was so angry.

463
00:37:00,556 --> 00:37:02,387
They should be home by now.

464
00:37:04,516 --> 00:37:06,746
You don't suppose
that they've gone into the...

465
00:37:08,436 --> 00:37:09,835
The North Woods.

466
00:37:09,916 --> 00:37:11,588
No, no. They wouldn't
have gone there.

467
00:37:11,676 --> 00:37:14,634
I've told them 100 times
not to go
anywhere near there.

468
00:37:15,996 --> 00:37:17,634
What have I done?

469
00:37:18,556 --> 00:37:21,309
Heaven help us. My children!

470
00:37:21,396 --> 00:37:22,590
Maria.

471
00:37:43,236 --> 00:37:45,306
<i>[woman moaning]</i>

472
00:37:51,796 --> 00:37:54,390
<i>[woman cackling]</i>

473
00:37:56,476 --> 00:37:58,353
<i>[man laughing]</i>

474
00:37:59,796 --> 00:38:02,754
[wind howling]

475
00:38:06,196 --> 00:38:08,426
<i>[woman screaming]</i>

476
00:38:11,836 --> 00:38:16,114
(Mother)
Hansel, Gretel,
where are you?

477
00:38:19,516 --> 00:38:21,427
[loon calling]

478
00:38:22,276 --> 00:38:24,949
Hansel! Gretel!

479
00:38:25,076 --> 00:38:28,671
Please come home.
I'm sorry.

480
00:38:28,756 --> 00:38:31,873
It's too dark.
No one could find them
in that forest tonight.

481
00:38:31,956 --> 00:38:33,469
Poor Hansel and Gretel.

482
00:38:33,956 --> 00:38:35,275
My little babies.

483
00:38:35,356 --> 00:38:38,393
lf anything should
happen to them,
I'd never forgive myself.

484
00:38:38,476 --> 00:38:40,865
Don't blame yourself.
You were upset.

485
00:38:41,196 --> 00:38:43,312
It's an evil forest.

486
00:38:43,676 --> 00:38:45,871
Many children have
disappeared there.

487
00:38:45,956 --> 00:38:48,709
There are no paths.
It's easy to become lost.

488
00:38:48,796 --> 00:38:52,027
An old woman once told me
there's a witch who lives

489
00:38:52,116 --> 00:38:54,710
deep in the North Woods
and demons as well.

490
00:38:54,796 --> 00:38:55,945
Superstition.

491
00:38:56,876 --> 00:38:58,594
Tonight, we will pray
for their safety.

492
00:38:58,676 --> 00:39:00,348
Tomorrow, I will set out
and find them.

493
00:39:00,436 --> 00:39:01,585
Come home.

494
00:39:09,156 --> 00:39:10,908
Come on, little sparks.

495
00:39:12,516 --> 00:39:16,145
Catch on fire.
Light these twigs.

496
00:39:16,796 --> 00:39:17,785
[grunting]

497
00:39:19,596 --> 00:39:21,427
I think we've got it.

498
00:39:25,036 --> 00:39:28,665
Yes, we're going
to have a fire.

499
00:39:30,396 --> 00:39:31,670
[sighing]

500
00:39:43,076 --> 00:39:46,113
<i>(female voice)</i>
<i>Gretel.</i>

501
00:39:49,836 --> 00:39:54,193
<i>Hansel.</i>

502
00:39:57,796 --> 00:39:59,388
[woman laughing]

503
00:39:59,556 --> 00:40:01,387
Mama? Papa?

504
00:40:05,516 --> 00:40:07,871
I shouldn't have
listened to you.

505
00:40:08,876 --> 00:40:10,912
I hope no goblin gets me.

506
00:40:12,316 --> 00:40:14,989
No goblin will get you
while I'm around.

507
00:40:16,196 --> 00:40:19,233
Sit close to me.
I'll protect you.

508
00:40:21,076 --> 00:40:24,148
<i>(male voice)</i>
<i>Hansel.</i>

509
00:40:25,756 --> 00:40:28,953
<i>Gretel.</i>

510
00:40:35,196 --> 00:40:37,869
<i>[man laughing]</i>

511
00:40:38,956 --> 00:40:40,947
[birds chirping]

512
00:41:36,996 --> 00:41:40,466
I dreamt that angels came
to protect us last night.

513
00:41:41,196 --> 00:41:44,427
Beautiful angels.
A boy and a girl.

514
00:41:45,596 --> 00:41:47,473
Maybe it wasn't a dream.

515
00:41:48,036 --> 00:41:49,185
We're safe.

516
00:41:56,276 --> 00:41:58,949
Mother and Father
must be very worried.

517
00:41:59,196 --> 00:42:00,788
Time to go home.

518
00:42:06,036 --> 00:42:09,870
I'm hungry.
I wish we still had
those berries.

519
00:42:22,476 --> 00:42:24,148
[birds chirping]

520
00:42:34,716 --> 00:42:36,274
Stephan. Stephan.

521
00:42:37,276 --> 00:42:39,073
Please let me come with you.

522
00:42:39,236 --> 00:42:42,228
No.
lf they find their way home,
it's best that you're here.

523
00:42:42,316 --> 00:42:43,305
[sighing]

524
00:43:46,636 --> 00:43:49,469
Look. Do you see that?

525
00:43:50,276 --> 00:43:53,825
Yes. Yes, l--I see it.

526
00:44:43,276 --> 00:44:46,507
Everything looks like
cookies and candies.

527
00:44:57,276 --> 00:44:58,914
They are candies.

528
00:44:59,916 --> 00:45:01,269
Hmm, lemon.

529
00:45:01,836 --> 00:45:04,953
Hansel,
how can you be so bold?

530
00:45:05,356 --> 00:45:06,869
Who knows who may live here?

531
00:45:08,596 --> 00:45:11,508
Well, I don't see anyone.
Aren't you hungry?

532
00:45:16,476 --> 00:45:17,545
Hmm.

533
00:45:18,236 --> 00:45:19,589
So good.

534
00:45:38,956 --> 00:45:39,945
[crunching]

535
00:45:40,956 --> 00:45:42,674
Gretel, it's real.

536
00:45:52,436 --> 00:45:56,349
The whole house is made
from cookies and candies.

537
00:46:02,996 --> 00:46:05,305
Hansel, look, lemon sticks!

538
00:46:16,396 --> 00:46:18,626
Welcome, children.

539
00:46:19,356 --> 00:46:22,393
Oh, poor darlings,
you must be starved.

540
00:46:22,476 --> 00:46:26,185
Oh, well, you've come
to the right place.

541
00:46:26,476 --> 00:46:29,468
Everything here
is good to eat.

542
00:46:30,796 --> 00:46:34,755
Oh, my name is Grizelda.

543
00:46:38,796 --> 00:46:40,434
Come here, little pretty.

544
00:46:42,036 --> 00:46:44,072
What is your name, child?

545
00:46:44,436 --> 00:46:45,585
Gretel, ma'am.

546
00:46:45,676 --> 00:46:47,587
And this is my brother,
Hansel.

547
00:46:47,956 --> 00:46:49,230
Oh!

548
00:46:50,436 --> 00:46:55,066
Gretel and Hansel.

549
00:46:57,756 --> 00:46:59,747
Your house is so beautiful.

550
00:46:59,836 --> 00:47:00,871
Well.

551
00:47:00,956 --> 00:47:02,674
Are you a candy maker?

552
00:47:02,996 --> 00:47:05,590
Oh, my, yes.

553
00:47:07,636 --> 00:47:09,672
And a baker, too.

554
00:47:11,196 --> 00:47:14,029
♪ Sugar and spice
and everything nice ♪

555
00:47:14,116 --> 00:47:16,835
♪ That's what
my house is made of ♪

556
00:47:16,916 --> 00:47:19,669
♪ Gingerbread girls
with strawberry curls ♪

557
00:47:19,756 --> 00:47:22,270
♪ That's what
my house is made of ♪

558
00:47:22,356 --> 00:47:25,075
♪ So, please come inside ♪

559
00:47:25,156 --> 00:47:27,875
♪ I'll help you decide ♪

560
00:47:27,956 --> 00:47:31,392
♪ I'm full of
delicious surprises ♪

561
00:47:31,476 --> 00:47:33,592
♪ And delicious disguises ♪

562
00:47:46,076 --> 00:47:48,636
♪ I love to cook ♪

563
00:47:48,716 --> 00:47:51,310
♪ and serve you little dears ♪

564
00:47:51,396 --> 00:47:54,274
♪ So tender and slender ♪

565
00:47:54,356 --> 00:47:57,234
♪ and hungry, it appears ♪

566
00:47:57,316 --> 00:47:59,876
♪ Apricot custard
and lemon meringue ♪

567
00:47:59,956 --> 00:48:02,595
♪ Raspberry strawberry torte ♪

568
00:48:02,676 --> 00:48:05,236
♪ Butterscotch pudding
and apple soufflé ♪

569
00:48:05,316 --> 00:48:07,830
♪ Marzipan, hazelnut,
mocha parfait ♪

570
00:48:07,916 --> 00:48:10,430
♪ And if you want more ♪

571
00:48:10,516 --> 00:48:13,474
♪ try the gingerbread door ♪

572
00:48:13,556 --> 00:48:18,471
♪ My dears, my pie,
my apple-raisin tart ♪

573
00:48:18,796 --> 00:48:21,435
♪ My cake, my best ♪

574
00:48:21,516 --> 00:48:24,508
♪ I cross my chocolate heart ♪

575
00:48:24,596 --> 00:48:26,985
♪ My house is yours ♪

576
00:48:27,076 --> 00:48:30,113
♪ You're welcome
and you're sweet ♪

577
00:48:30,196 --> 00:48:32,915
♪ So tender, so slender ♪

578
00:48:32,996 --> 00:48:35,794
♪ You need some more to eat ♪

