00:48:38,716 --> 00:48:43,153
♪ You need some more to eat ♪

581
00:48:43,436 --> 00:48:46,189
♪ Some more to eat ♪

582
00:48:46,276 --> 00:48:48,665
♪ Some more to eat ♪

583
00:48:48,996 --> 00:48:52,272
♪ Some more to eat ♪

584
00:48:52,356 --> 00:48:55,029
♪ To add some more meat ♪♪

585
00:48:56,236 --> 00:48:57,908
[birds chirping]

586
00:49:10,556 --> 00:49:13,593
''No sooner had his lips
touched hers

587
00:49:13,676 --> 00:49:16,315
''then Briar Rose
opened her eyes

588
00:49:16,396 --> 00:49:19,672
woke up and smiled sweetly.''

589
00:49:20,996 --> 00:49:25,945
Oh, Gretel, you are so sweet,
just like my candies.

590
00:49:27,116 --> 00:49:28,788
Now where was l?

591
00:49:31,156 --> 00:49:33,511
''They went
downstairs together.

592
00:49:34,036 --> 00:49:38,791
''And then
the King and the Queen
and the whole court woke up.

593
00:49:38,876 --> 00:49:42,755
And they all stared
at each other in amazement!''

594
00:49:43,396 --> 00:49:47,514
Oh, poor little Hansel.
You are so painfully thin.

595
00:49:47,596 --> 00:49:49,826
Here, won't you have
another doughnut?

596
00:49:50,836 --> 00:49:52,474
Not at the moment, thank you.

597
00:49:52,556 --> 00:49:53,671
[burping]

598
00:49:54,956 --> 00:49:58,028
My, what perfect
manners you have.

599
00:49:59,796 --> 00:50:03,266
All right. Well,
I'll just put them over here.

600
00:50:03,356 --> 00:50:05,506
You can have one
whenever you want one.

601
00:50:05,596 --> 00:50:07,666
I made them
especially for you, children.

602
00:50:07,756 --> 00:50:11,829
Oh, I'm so glad you children
decided to spend the night.

603
00:50:11,916 --> 00:50:14,635
The whole court looked
at each other in amazement?

604
00:50:14,716 --> 00:50:15,990
Just... Here.

605
00:50:16,076 --> 00:50:19,955
''The horses stood up
and shook themselves.

606
00:50:20,036 --> 00:50:22,755
''The flies on the wall
started crawling

607
00:50:23,636 --> 00:50:27,629
and the fire in the kitchen
flamed up and cooked
the children.''

608
00:50:29,676 --> 00:50:31,553
I mean, the chicken.

609
00:50:32,276 --> 00:50:34,028
Cooked the chicken.

610
00:50:34,596 --> 00:50:35,824
[laughing]

611
00:50:36,596 --> 00:50:39,508
Are you children comfortable?
Would you like
four or five more pillows?

612
00:50:39,596 --> 00:50:42,156
No, thank you.
Finish the story, please.

613
00:50:42,236 --> 00:50:43,908
Yes, please.
Yes.

614
00:50:44,236 --> 00:50:45,271
[sighing]

615
00:50:45,356 --> 00:50:47,745
''The cook began
to roast again.

616
00:50:49,156 --> 00:50:51,795
''The roast began
to cook again.

617
00:50:51,876 --> 00:50:55,312
''And, uh,
the, uh, Prince and Briar Rose

618
00:50:55,396 --> 00:50:56,988
''were married in splendour

619
00:50:57,076 --> 00:51:00,386
and lived happily to the end
of their little lives.''

620
00:51:00,876 --> 00:51:03,071
''Their long lives.'' Yes.

621
00:51:04,396 --> 00:51:06,034
That was a good story.

622
00:51:06,116 --> 00:51:08,107
Yes, yes.

623
00:51:12,116 --> 00:51:15,506
Grizelda,
what's that you wear
around your neck?

624
00:51:16,796 --> 00:51:20,027
Oh,
this is my eyeglass, child.

625
00:51:20,396 --> 00:51:23,194
It helps me to
see things close up.

626
00:51:30,476 --> 00:51:33,832
When I take my glass away,
I don't see quite as well.

627
00:51:34,076 --> 00:51:37,068
That, that's what happens
when you get as old as me.

628
00:51:38,116 --> 00:51:40,949
But my nose,
now that's a different story.

629
00:51:41,116 --> 00:51:43,346
I have a very good
sense of smell.

630
00:51:43,516 --> 00:51:45,791
It helps me to cook up
all my goodies.

631
00:51:46,276 --> 00:51:47,629
(Gretel)
Can I look through it?

632
00:51:47,716 --> 00:51:50,071
Oh, no, no, dear.
It's fragile.

633
00:51:50,636 --> 00:51:54,265
And Grandmother Grizelda
wouldn't want to
let it out of her sight.

634
00:51:54,356 --> 00:51:57,666
Yes, good night,
my little cupcakes.
Sleep tight

635
00:51:57,756 --> 00:51:59,951
and don't let
the bedbugs bite.

636
00:52:04,876 --> 00:52:09,392
Could we have
pancakes and jam
for breakfast tomorrow,

637
00:52:09,476 --> 00:52:11,194
Grandmother Grizelda?

638
00:52:11,316 --> 00:52:12,988
Well,
of course you will, honey.

639
00:52:13,076 --> 00:52:15,795
You can have anything
your plump little
heart desires.

640
00:52:15,876 --> 00:52:19,789
You'll have
stacks and stacks of pancakes
and three kinds of jam.

641
00:52:19,876 --> 00:52:23,152
And--and--and Gretel and l
will cook up
a wondrous breakfast.

642
00:52:23,596 --> 00:52:24,995
Won't we, Gretel?

643
00:52:25,116 --> 00:52:26,435
Yes, Grizelda.

644
00:52:26,676 --> 00:52:28,587
Good night. And thank you.

645
00:52:28,676 --> 00:52:30,109
You're welcome as pie.

646
00:52:32,436 --> 00:52:33,835
Welcome as pie.

647
00:52:33,916 --> 00:52:35,269
[laughing]

648
00:52:35,596 --> 00:52:39,794
Good night, good night.
Good night, good night.

649
00:52:46,956 --> 00:52:50,232
Hansel, you called
Grizelda ''Grandmother.''

650
00:52:51,076 --> 00:52:53,749
But she's not our grandmother,
is she?

651
00:52:55,356 --> 00:52:57,187
Our grandparents
are in heaven,

652
00:52:57,396 --> 00:52:59,227
so she can be
our new grandmother.

653
00:52:59,996 --> 00:53:00,985
Oh.

654
00:53:07,436 --> 00:53:09,154
This bed is so comfortable.

655
00:53:10,116 --> 00:53:11,469
It's like a cloud.

656
00:53:12,076 --> 00:53:14,112
I wish we could
live here all the time.

657
00:53:14,756 --> 00:53:16,508
What about Mother and Father?

658
00:53:18,636 --> 00:53:20,194
Wouldn't you
like to live here

659
00:53:20,276 --> 00:53:22,073
and eat the good things
Grizelda cooks

660
00:53:22,156 --> 00:53:24,670
and have her read us
stories every night?

661
00:53:27,916 --> 00:53:31,704
This is the most
wonderful house
in the whole world.

662
00:53:47,556 --> 00:53:49,274
[crickets chirping]

663
00:53:53,196 --> 00:53:55,187
[Grizelda laughing]

664
00:54:03,236 --> 00:54:04,430
[whispering]
Hansel.

665
00:54:07,716 --> 00:54:09,274
Hansel, wake up.

666
00:54:10,476 --> 00:54:13,991
Put some more
marshmallow sauce
on my fudge.

667
00:54:15,276 --> 00:54:16,868
Oh, Hansel.

668
00:54:26,916 --> 00:54:28,668
♪♪[Grizelda chanting]

669
00:54:59,676 --> 00:55:02,429
(Grizelda)
''At the midnight hour

670
00:55:02,516 --> 00:55:05,030
''when no one can see

671
00:55:05,596 --> 00:55:08,349
''I speak my witch's chant

672
00:55:08,436 --> 00:55:10,950
''with a goblin's glee

673
00:55:12,396 --> 00:55:17,106
''and three and four
this witch's lore

674
00:55:17,436 --> 00:55:21,827
''and five and six,
my witchy tricks

675
00:55:22,356 --> 00:55:25,826
''And nine is one
and ten is none!

676
00:55:25,916 --> 00:55:30,194
''And seven is nil
or what I will

677
00:55:30,436 --> 00:55:34,315
''And thus I chant
till dawn of day

678
00:55:34,396 --> 00:55:38,947
''These children
shall be mine!

679
00:55:39,316 --> 00:55:43,070
''So, dream away,
you little sheep

680
00:55:43,476 --> 00:55:48,152
''for soon you'll sleep
your last long sleep

681
00:55:48,476 --> 00:55:53,311
''And hence become part
of my gingerbread fence

682
00:55:53,756 --> 00:55:56,907
''Oh, how well I will dine

683
00:55:57,076 --> 00:56:01,354
on young flesh so divine!''

684
00:56:01,836 --> 00:56:03,269
[sniffing]

685
00:56:03,956 --> 00:56:06,993
I know you're there.

686
00:56:08,316 --> 00:56:10,591
I can smell you.

687
00:56:15,196 --> 00:56:16,311
[door closing]

688
00:56:23,436 --> 00:56:26,553
Hansel! Hansel!
Wake up! Hansel.

689
00:56:27,076 --> 00:56:28,191
What is it?

690
00:56:28,276 --> 00:56:30,267
She's a witch!
She's a witch!

691
00:56:31,236 --> 00:56:32,385
[door bursts open]

692
00:56:32,476 --> 00:56:33,545
[laughing]

693
00:56:33,636 --> 00:56:34,705
[screaming]

694
00:56:35,316 --> 00:56:38,353
''Hocus pocus, witch's spell

695
00:56:38,436 --> 00:56:43,032
Rope entwine his body welI''

696
00:56:43,276 --> 00:56:45,153
[laughing]

697
00:56:51,396 --> 00:56:53,751
Hansel, run!

698
00:56:54,516 --> 00:56:57,667
I can't. I can't move!

699
00:56:57,836 --> 00:57:01,909
''Rope restrain him,
Gretel, behave

700
00:57:01,996 --> 00:57:06,592
''He's my prey
and she's my slave

701
00:57:07,996 --> 00:57:12,467
''Hocus pocus, <i>malus locus</i>

702
00:57:12,596 --> 00:57:17,431
''Roucus volus, hocus pocus

703
00:57:42,396 --> 00:57:45,388
''You'll eat by day

704
00:57:46,956 --> 00:57:50,585
''And you'll eat by night

705
00:57:51,636 --> 00:57:53,467
''And in a week

706
00:57:53,836 --> 00:57:57,795
you'll be plump all right''

707
00:57:58,156 --> 00:57:59,828
[laughing]

708
00:58:02,676 --> 00:58:04,189
[birds chirping]

709
00:59:02,396 --> 00:59:04,114
[laughing]

710
00:59:53,156 --> 00:59:54,475
[grunts]

711
01:00:11,276 --> 01:00:12,595
[sighing]

712
01:00:26,116 --> 01:00:27,629
Hurry up, you little mouse.

713
01:00:27,716 --> 01:00:30,947
You're not washing
fast enough to keep up
with the great Grizelda.

714
01:00:31,036 --> 01:00:34,472
Well, let's see now.
Two and a half cups of milk.

715
01:00:34,796 --> 01:00:37,674
Make the curd separately,
dust with flour...

716
01:00:37,756 --> 01:00:40,190
Ooh, you're such
a lucky boy, Hansel.

717
01:00:40,276 --> 01:00:41,709
[laughing]

718
01:00:43,036 --> 01:00:45,869
I'm making you
a lemon-cream cake.

719
01:00:47,076 --> 01:00:48,828
I don't want
anything from you.

720
01:00:49,276 --> 01:00:50,789
Let me out of here!

721
01:00:53,156 --> 01:00:56,831
Uh, boysenberry, elderberry,

722
01:00:57,196 --> 01:00:58,914
blueberry,

723
01:00:59,076 --> 01:01:01,715
ooh, firm pears,

724
01:01:02,756 --> 01:01:05,987
crystallized ginger
and apple juice.

725
01:01:06,596 --> 01:01:09,429
Hansel, a gingered pear pie?

726
01:01:09,516 --> 01:01:13,270
Ooh, I've never made
one of those before.

727
01:01:13,876 --> 01:01:17,505
Or what about my delicious
bread-and-butter pudding

728
01:01:17,596 --> 01:01:18,995
with jam and meringue?

729
01:01:19,076 --> 01:01:21,670
I'll eat no more
of your cooking, witch!

730
01:01:22,276 --> 01:01:25,666
You'll eat what I tell you to,
when I tell you to.

731
01:01:25,756 --> 01:01:28,475
The only time
I'll let your little sister
stop her chores,

732
01:01:28,556 --> 01:01:30,228
is when you're eating.

733
01:01:30,436 --> 01:01:31,551
Understand?

734
01:01:32,076 --> 01:01:34,988
We've got to fatten
you up like a pig.

735
01:01:37,996 --> 01:01:40,988
Gretel, wash that pie plate
and be quick about it.

736
01:02:28,396 --> 01:02:31,786
You've still got
a whole barrel
of apples to do.

737
01:02:32,716 --> 01:02:34,707
At that rate
you'll never finish!

738
01:02:39,516 --> 01:02:40,710
Faster.

739
01:02:45,156 --> 01:02:46,589
[chuckling]

740
01:02:51,876 --> 01:02:55,505
You're not getting tired
of my delicious pies

741
01:02:55,596 --> 01:02:57,393
and puddings
are you, little Hansel?

742
01:02:57,476 --> 01:02:58,670
Give me your finger.

743
01:03:01,996 --> 01:03:03,395
Oh, my, my.

744
01:03:03,996 --> 01:03:06,794
You still need
some more fattening up

745
01:03:07,196 --> 01:03:10,871
before I bake you in my oven.

746
01:03:19,796 --> 01:03:21,468
[birds chirping]

747
01:03:22,596 --> 01:03:24,029
<i>(Hansel)</i>
<i>Help, Father!</i>

748
01:03:27,276 --> 01:03:29,836
<i>Father, help us.</i>

749
01:03:30,516 --> 01:03:31,744
<i>Father?</i>

750
01:03:32,356 --> 01:03:34,267
<i>Help us, please, Father.</i>

751
01:03:35,396 --> 01:03:36,715
<i>Please.</i>

752
01:03:37,476 --> 01:03:39,114
<i>Father, please.</i>

753
01:03:40,636 --> 01:03:44,515
<i>(raspy voice)</i>
<i>Father, help us.</i>

754
01:03:44,596 --> 01:03:46,427
<i>[voice laughing]</i>

755
01:03:51,716 --> 01:03:52,990
Hansel!

756
01:03:53,076 --> 01:03:54,987
<i>(Gretel)</i>
<i>Please, Father,</i>
<i>come and get us!</i>

757
01:03:58,516 --> 01:03:59,551
Gretel!

758
01:03:59,636 --> 01:04:02,514
<i>Please, Father,</i>
<i>come and get us!</i>

759
01:04:04,436 --> 01:04:06,074
<i>Please.</i>

760
01:04:14,836 --> 01:04:17,304
You're eating too slowly,
my little man.

761
01:04:17,396 --> 01:04:18,795
Hurry up and finish.

762
01:04:18,876 --> 01:04:21,629
Your sister has
lots of chores to do for me.

